Freishein/Permit should be obtained by the operator directly from Austrian Tax Authorities. If the Freishein/Permit is not presented, the supplier under no exception will charge WFS MOT which inturn will be passed through to our customer. If MOT is charged the operator will need to reclaim directly with the Austrian Tax Authorities. Effective 1 October 2022 Austrian legislation has introduced a national emissions trading scheme. All product where mineral oil tax is incurred the CO2 emissions fee will be charged, including both Jet-A and Avgas. If you have any questions on how to obtain a Freishein/Permit or any general enquiries, please do not hesitate to contact your local fuel logistics team on fuel24@wfscorp.com

column7: ** Be aware IATA: MLH & BSL are for the SAME airport. Please read info below to confirm the correct IATA to use. *** 1) Operating Hours: From 05.00 to 23.00 Local time 2) Ramps serviced: Unable to Access the Jet Aviation Ramp Please be aware flights operating to BSL or MLH are separated based on the a/c registration or who the handling agent is: a) A/C registered in Switzerland (HB-) will always be refuelled at BSL. b) A/C registered anywhere other than Switzerland will be refuelled at MLH unless the flight is operating to a destination within Switzerland - then the fuelling location will be BSL (VAT and MOT will also be charged. c) if the A/C is being handled by Flugchule Basel, AMAC Aerospace, Air Service Basel or any Swiss handling agent then the fuelling location will be BSL (be sure to ask the customer this prior to quoting / arranging the uplift). d) if the A/C registration is French (F-) then the fuelling location will always be MLH. e) A/C in maintenance will be fuelled in BSL. Customers should note that if the ticket or documentation completed on the ground proves that the uplift was fuelled at BSL or MLH based on the above conditions (destination of flight, tail registration, the fueller of the aircraft, maintenance fuelling), then the order will need to be amended to the location specified on the ticket, which will affect the taxes. In the event that any documentation is incorrect/not completed, WFS will pass on applicable taxes and disputes have to be directed to the local authority. 3) Additional Information: If applicable, Out of hours fees may apply. Fees are subject to change without prior notice. For more information please contact your local fuel logistics team on fuel24@wfscorp.com

column7: 1) ITP Operating hours: From 5:00 AM to 11:00 PM . Out-of-hours possible on notice 2) Ramps serviced: WFS has access to All ramps at the airport. REFUELLING NOT AVBL ON MIKE HELIPORT - 3) Additional Information: No fuel (minimum 30 minutes notice if no fuel is required) , Over wing and Out-of-hours fees may apply. De-fueling NOT possible Over time subject to 2 conditions : (a) the aircraft should leave immediately after the refuelling (not the day after or later in the morning, during the opening hours) (b) the request must be done not after 4:00 AM, because the duty staff has 1 hour duration to arrive to the Aircraft, therefore 5:00 max. And the station opens at 5:00 so same hour. Please note there is a specific process at NCE airport, whenever a customer lands during night time (11:00PM to 5:00AM local time) and requests fuel. If the AC is due to depart immediately, the handling company needs to call the airport (PCE) which in turn will contact directly the ITP on-duty personal. This person is required to be on site within the hour to start refuelling the AC *** ** WFS Self Service Pumps** The Self-Service bowser at LFMN requires a specific card which is issued after the Operator has completed a training program. Only until this is done is that the Operator will be able to use the AVCARD on WFS Self-Serve pumps. Prior this, please kindly keep requesting your fuel releases. Notice: As NCE/LFMN experiences a high volume of traffic during the busy summer season, we kindly recommend uplifting fuel upon arrival to help ensure a smooth and timely departure For more information please contact your local fuel logistics team on fuel24@wfscorp.com

column7: 1) Minimum Notice Required: 24 hours operation. 2) Ramps serviced: Most ramps 3) Additional Information: Over Wing fuelling available. Aircraft operating Non-Commercial flights with or without an Air Operator's Certificate are liable to paying the Special Excise Tax. Additionally, 24% VAT will be added on total invoice value. In order to avoid such charges, a copy of the Air Operator's Certificate (AOC), formally translated into English, or any other document that Local Customs' Authorities may request, must be submitted at the point of delivery or upon request. Customs fee may be charged per uplift (under 500USG) to general aviation and commercial customers not flying there regularly. The fee does not apply to commercial contracted customers. No fuel fees may be applicable Military flights are exempted from MOT but they have to pay VAT, except in cases that the military flight is on behalf of NATO (customer will have to show NATO exemption document) For more information please contact your local fuel logistics team on fuel24@wfscorp.com

De-icing available at extra cost. Parking for more than 60 mins, additional fee apply. No catering service, hotel bookings or water and toilet service available. The aircraft operator shall document fulfilment of the requirements stated in AD 2.23 p 3 (https://ais.avinor.no/no/AIP/View/41/aip/ad/ensb/EN_AD_2_ENSB_en.pdf) to CAA Norway at least 14 days prior to commencing operations. CAA Norway will, after evaluating the documentation and finding it adequate, issue a letter of compliance. A copy of this letter has to be carried by the crew and presented to local airport authorities or representatives of CAA Norway on request. Please also be aware that you will have to apply to the Norwegian CAA 48 hours in advance to fly to Svalbard. Contact is traffic.permission@caa.no . To request arrival- and departure time, contact Nordic Airport Coordination at acn@airportcoordination.com . Domestic flights will incur, CO2 tax and V.A.T. For more information please contact your local fuel logistics team on fuel24@wfscorp.com

column7: Be aware IATA: MLH & BSL are for the SAME airport. Please read info below to confirm the correct IATA to use. 2) RAMPS SERVICED: Please be aware flights operating to BSL or MLH are separated based on the a/c registration or who the handling agent is: a) A/C registered in Switzerland (HB-) will always be refuelled at BSL. b) A/C registered anywhere other than Switzerland will be refuelled at MLH unless the flight is operating to a destination within Switzerland - then the fuelling location will be BSL (VAT and MOT will also be charged. c) if the A/C is being handled by Flugchule Basel, AMAC Aerospace, Air Service Basel or any Swiss handling agent then the fuelling location will be BSL (be sure to ask the customer this prior to quoting / arranging the uplift). d) if the A/C registration is French (F-) then the fuelling location will always be MLH. e) A/C in maintenance will be fuelled in BSL. Customers should note that if the ticket proves that the uplift was fuelled at BSL or MLH based on the above conditions (destination of flight, tail registration, the fueller of the aircraft, maintenance fuelling) then the order will need to be amended to the location specified on the ticket, which will affect the taxes. ** FOR VAT EXEMPTION PLEASE PROVIDE A VALID AOC AT TIME OF REFUELING. ASK PIC TO MAKE SURE THAT 'INTERNATIONAL FLIGHT' IS WRITTEN ON THE DELIVERY TICKET! ** For more information please contact your local fuel logistics team on fuel24@wfscorp.com

Please read info below to confirm the correct IATA to use. *** 1) Operating Hours: 5am to 11pm Local time 2) Ramps serviced: Unable to Access the Jet Aviation Ramp Please be aware flights operating to BSL or MLH are separated based on the a/c registration or who the handling agent is: a) A/C registered in Switzerland (HB-) will always be refuelled at BSL. b) A/C registered anywhere other than Switzerland will be refuelled at MLH unless the flight is operating to a destination within Switzerland - then the fuelling location will be BSL (VAT and MOT will also be charged. c) if the A/C is being handled by Flugchule Basel, AMAC Aerospace, Air Service Basel or any Swiss handling agent then the fuelling location will be BSL (be sure to ask the customer this prior to quoting / arranging the uplift). d) if the A/C registration is French (F-) then the fuelling location will always be MLH. e) A/C in maintenance will be fuelled in BSL. Customers should note that if the ticket or documentation completed on the ground proves that the uplift was fuelled at BSL or MLH based on the above conditions (destination of flight, tail registration, the fueller of the aircraft, maintenance fuelling), then the order will need to be amended to the location specified on the ticket, which will affect the taxes. In the event that any documentation is incorrect/not completed, WFS will pass on applicable taxes and disputes have to be directed to the local authority. For more information please contact your local fuel logistics team on fuel24@wfscorp.com 3) Additional Information: Fees apply. Fees are subject to change without prior notice. For more information please contact your local fuel logistics team on fuel24@wfscorp.com </font
